        "title": "[codex] Add remote wacli support and trust crawler status",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add manifest-level SSH execution so crawlers can run on a remote machine through local `ssh`\n- enable `wacli` as a remote WhatsApp crawler with configurable SSH target, optional remote run-as user, and named account\n- normalize `wacli doctor --json` into CrawlBar status, and trust crawler-reported `state` so current archives do not stay yellow because of older freshness metadata\n\n## Why\nSome crawl stores live on another machine, especially WhatsApp archives tied to a logged-in host. CrawlBar should not require the crawler binary or data store to live on the Mac running the menu bar app. It also should not override a crawler's explicit current status with stale heuristics when the crawler owns the status contract.\n\n## Validation\n- `swift run crawlbar-selftest`\n- `swift build`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `swift run crawlbarctl metadata --diagnostics`\n- live smoke: `crawlbarctl status --app discrawl --json` reports `state: current`\n- live smoke: `crawlbarctl status --app gitcrawl --json` reports `state: current`\n- live smoke: external remote `wacli` manifests report current status and search works through SSH\n",
